The developed method was proved to be effective in the analysis of AMT in Atomox Apex® capsules and human plasma. When analyzing Atomox Apex® capsules, the concentration of AMT was determined with %R ± SD of 99.79 ± 0.47. A comparison with a previously documented method [16] revealed no significant differences, confirming the reliability and accuracy of the developed method (Table 3
                        ). When investigating plasma samples spiked with AMT, the method exhibited exceptional efficiency. The %R fell within the range of 92.31–99.93 % and the coefficient of variation (CV) values were less than 10 %, signifying the method's accuracy and precision in quantifying AMT within plasma samples (Table 4
                        ).
